issue.message: Exception requires API level 19 (current min is 19): `java.lang.ReflectiveOperationException`, and having a surrounding/preceding version check **does** not help since prior to API level 19, just **loading** the class will cause a crash. Consider marking the surrounding class with `RequiresApi(19)` to ensure that the class is never loaded except when on API 19 or higher.

This method should be called `getWillSuppressErrorPage` such that `willSuppressErrorPage` can be accessed as a property from Kotlin; see https://android.github.io/kotlin-guides/interop.html#property-prefixes

Functional interface parameters (such as parameter 1, "callback", in org.chromium.support_lib_boundary.WebMessagePortBoundaryInterface.setWebMessageCallback) should be last to improve Kotlin interoperability; see https://kotlinlang.org/docs/reference/java-interop.html#sam-conversions
